  <!-- ===== Level 14: Dragon Wings ===== -->
  <element name="Dragon Wings" type="Archetype Feature" source="Player's Handbook (2024)" id="ID_WOTC_PHB24_SORCERER_DRACONIC_FEATURE_DRAGON_WINGS">
    <description>
      <p><strong>Bonus Action.</strong> You manifest draconic wings that last for 1 hour or until you dismiss them (no action required). For the duration, you have a Fly Speed of 60 feet.</p>
      <p>Once you use this feature, you canâ€™t use it again until you finish a Long Rest, unless you spend 3 Sorcery Points (no action required) to restore your use of it.</p>
    </description>
    <sheet action="Bonus Action" usage="1/Long Rest">
      <description>Manifest wings for 1 hour (or until dismissed): Fly Speed 60 ft. You can restore a use by spending 3 Sorcery Points.</description>
    </sheet>
  </element>

  <!-- ===== Level 18: Dragon Companion ===== -->
  <element name="Dragon Companion" type="Archetype Feature" source="Player's Handbook (2024)" id="ID_WOTC_PHB24_SORCERER_DRACONIC_FEATURE_DRAGON_COMPANION">
    <description>
      <p>You can cast <em>Summon Dragon</em> without a Material component. You can also cast it once without expending a spell slot; you regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a Long Rest.</p>
      <p>Whenever you start casting the spell, you can modify it so that it doesnâ€™t require Concentration; if you do so, its duration becomes 1 minute for that casting.</p>
    </description>
    <sheet>
      <description>You can cast Summon Dragon without the Material component and 1 per Long Rest without expending a spell slot; you can also make that casting not require Concentration, but the duration becomes 1 minute.</description>
    </sheet>
    <rules>
      <grant type="Spell" id="ID_PHB24_SPELL_SUMMON_DRAGON" prepared="true" spellcasting="Sorcerer" />
    </rules>
  </element>
</elements>



